The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On a good length on off, Burns taps it towards point and takes a run.
Good length delivery on middle, Warner defends it off the back foot.
Warner defends this good length delivery off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Burns flicks it to mid-wicket.

Not Out! That looked out from one of the angle but the benefit of the doubt goes to the batter. The third umpire took a long time in making that decision. Coming to the delivery, a flighted ball it was. Burns turned it towards mid-wicket and went off for the second run, a risky one. Yasir Shah gets to the ball and fires the throw at the non-striker's end. He hits the stumps and the umpire refers it upstairs. Looks safe from one angle but mighty close from another one. Not out says the third umpire and Warner's march towards his century continues.
Flighted delivery on middle, Burns sweeps it through square leg for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, David defends it off the back foot.
Flatter one on off, pushed towards cover.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman.
Outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Full delivery on middle, Burns drives it through mid on for a boundary.
On a good length and outside off, Burns lets it go.
Short of a length delivery, Burns pulls it towards square leg for a single.
Length delivery on off, David guides it towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
On the pads, Warner tucks it behind square leg for a single.
Flighted on off, David pushes it towards mid off.
Flatter one on middle, Warner lunges forward and keeps it out.
Quicker one this time, Warner blocks it with ease.
Full and on middle, Warner pushes it towards long on for a single. Just 3 away from his ton.
Full on the pads, flicked towards mid on.
Flighted on middle, Burns comes forward and defends it easily.
Short and outside off, Warner pulls but straight to mid on.
Full and on off, driven straight to mid off.
Shortish length ball on middle, Warner tucks it wide of mid on for a single.

Crunched nicely. Full ball outside off, Burns creams it through cover-point. The ball races towards the fence but the fielder chases it down and saves a single. Warner on strike for the last two balls before Tea.
Good length ball around off, Warner keeps it out. Not looking in any hurry there.
Warner has to wait! A good length ball around off, Warner taps it through point and takes the single. He thinks for the second but decides against the second. TEA ON DAY 2.
Good length ball outside off, Warner is in no hurry as he lets it go to the keeper.
In the channel outside off, Warner makes another leave.
Fullish ball just outside off, Warner drives it firmly but straight to cover.
Good length ball around, tapped towards point by Warner. The wait for that single continues.
On middle, Warner taps it onto the pitch on the leg side and shouts a loud no.
Fuller and outside off, Warner leaves it alone. So the wait goes to the next over.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Shortish ball on off, Burns goes back and taps it through point. The crowd erupts as Warner is back on the strike.
Flighted and fuller, Warner comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and on middle, Warner cuts but straight to point.
On middle, pushed towards mid on. Nice tight stuff from the Pakistan bowlers.

There it is. Century no. 22 for David Warner. Forget about the struggles during the Ashes. The southpaw is back to his best. What a fabulous innings this has been from him. The leaping celebration with the punch of the helmet. The crowd stands and applauds the top innings from Warner. What a moment this is for him. He gets a hug from his opening partner. He is taking his time. Coming to the ball, it is on the pads, Warner easily nudges it towards the square leg region for a single.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards cover.
Fullish and on off, Warner keeps it out. A massive no ball that one.
On the pads, turned towards mid-wicket for a single.
In the channel outside off, Burns lets it be.
Around off on a length, Burns blocks it out.
Fullish and on off, Burns comes forward and blocks.
Full delivery on off, Burns drives it towards covers where the fielder misfields and it goes through him. The batters return for the second to bring 200-run stand.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off. Warner goes back and cuts it through point to bag a boundary.
On off, it is defended.
Full and on middle, Warner eases it through mid on for a single.
Flatter one on middle, pushed towards the right of the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Fuller ball just outside off, Burns guides it towards point.
Fullish length ball on off, Warner blocks it out.
Shortish length ball on off, Warner turns it towards mid-wicket and scampers back for the second.
Good length ball just around off, Warner comes on the front foot and blocks.
Short and wide outside off, Warner cuts but finds the fielder.
Fullish ball in the channel. Warner covers his stumps, hides his bat and then lets the ball pass to the keeper.
Fullish and on off, Warner blocks it towards mid off and once again makes a loud call to his partner at the other end.
Flighted ball on off, Burns taps it almost towards point for a single. A misfield there but no extra runs.
Fuller and on off, Warner drives it wide of mid off who makes a tumbling stop but a single is taken as it was wide of him.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
A solid prod forward and defense from Burns to this fuller ball on middle.
Flighted and on middle, Burns eases a single to move closer to his century through mid on.

FOUR! Shout for the catch it but it is wide of the mid off fielder. Flighted ball around off, Warner has his dancing shoes on to time it right of the bowler and just left of the mid off fielder. The ball races to the fence. Australia trail by just 25 runs now.
Good length ball around off, Joe taps it towards cover
Around off, Burns keeps it out.
Fullish and on the pads, pushed towards mid on.
Around off and middle, Burns punches it well but straight to mid on.
Another firm drive but straight to the fielder at cover.
Fullish and just outside off, Burns keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Warner drives it through mid on for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Burns drives it through mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on off, Warner defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, David drives it back towards the bowler where Yasir Shah tries to stop the ball but it hits his foot and goes towards mid-wicket. No run taken.
Shortish length on the stumps line, pushed towards cover.
On middle, Warner keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards cover.
Fuller ball on off, Burns drives it straight back to the bowler.
Good length ball around off, Burns gets right behind the line of the ball to defend it out.
Short and outside off, Burns smacks it through the point region but just a single as there is protection in the deep.
Bouncer but down the leg side. Warner ducks under it.
Full and on middle, Warner nudges it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Short and on the pads, Warner turns it behind square leg and takes a single. Burns wanted the second but Warner sends him back.
Fuller and outside off, Burns drives it straight to cover.
Quicker one and on the pads, Burns works it towards mid-wicket and takes a couple. Three away from a Test ton.
Flighted outside off, Burns pushes it towards point and looks for a run. Warner though sends him back.

OUT! Bowled him around his legs. Oh dear! No Test ton for the hometown boy. A loopy ball outside leg. Burns looks to sweep but drags the ball on the stumps off his gloves. He is distraught as he walks back. Deserved a Test ton in front of his home crowd. Pakistan though finally have a wicket. Yasir went round the wicket for this ball and the change of angle worked for him there. The massive 222-run stand is broken.
Full ball on middle, Marnus flicks it towards mid on where the fielder misfields and allows a couple to Labuschagne.
Short and outside off, Warner punches it nicely to beat the diving extra cover fielder for a couple. The deep cover fielder cuts it off.
Good length ball on off, Warner defends it out.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
In the channel outside off, Warner lets it go to the keeper.
Down the leg side. Warner looks to flick but misses.
Shortish length outside off, Warner pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Shortish length ball on middle, Warner goes back and pushes it through point for a single.
Flighted and fuller outside off, Labuschagne pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and wide, Labuschagne rocks back on and taps it through point for three.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Woah! Extra bounce there. And it beats everyone, the batter as well as the keeper. It pitches around off and bounces extra and beats the bat.
On the pads, Warner works it on the leg side to take a single.
Shortish length around off, Warner taps it towards point and takes off for a single. The fielder there scores a direct hit at the striker's end but Marnus is well in.
Good length ball around off, Labuschagne defends it out.
Shortish length ball around off, Marnus rides the bounce and defends it easily.
Good length ball around off, Labuschagne pushes it towards cover.

Four running runs. Second time in the day. A short ball on middle, Marnus pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. The mid-wicket fielder hares and pulls the ball before it can reach the fence. It won't matter as both the batters have run four.
Shortish ball around off, Labuschagne hops and keeps it out.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery on off, Warner looks to cut but misses it.
Full delivery on off, Warner drives it to mid off.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Warner comes down the track and plays it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it to mid off.
Floated delivery on off, Marnus defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball around off, Warner keeps it out.
Short and outside off, Warner cuts it through point for a single.
On a length on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Warner defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery outside off, Warner cuts it through point. The batsmen take a run. Australia lead by 1 run.
On a good length on off, Marnus keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Warner flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Full ball on middle, Marnus flicks but straight to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball on middle, Labuschagne comes forward and defends it.
Play and a miss! A flighted ball outside off, Marnus looks to drive but misses. Rizwan behind the wicket fails to gather that cleanly.
Full and outside off again, driven nicely but once again straight to mid off.
Fuller and around off, defended.
Short and outside off, cut to deep point for a single.
Full on the pads, ML flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Full and on middle, Warner works it towards square leg. Warner took off for the first run to see if he can get the second one. But it was not on the cards.
Shortish ball outside off, tapped straight to gully.
Good length ball on off, Labuschagne gets behind the line of the ball to defend it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
Flatter ball on middle, Warner directs it towards point for a single.
On off, ML keeps it out.
FOUR! Crunched! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne rocks on the back foot and crunches the punch through the extra cover region to bag his first boundary.
On the pads, Marnus this time turns it towards square leg for a single.
Short ball on off, Warner pulls it wide of long on and picks a couple. That did not come from the middle of the bat.

Huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is not moved. Flighted ball around off, Warner comes forward to defend but gets hit on the pads. Yasir along with the keeper makes loud appeal but the umpire does not agree with him. The skipper has a chat and then he decides against taking the review. The Ball Tracker rolls and shows that it would've been umpire's call on hitting the wicket.
Flighted ball on off, Marnus blocks it out.
Beaten! Shortish length ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to cut but fails to put any bat on ball.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the pads, turned towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on middle, Warner pushes it to mid on for nothing.
Flighted around off, Marnus comes forward and defends it out.
Flatter one on middle, Labuschagne stays back and blocks.
On off, Labuschagne defends it nicely.
On the pads, Marnus comes forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on the pads, tucked towards the leg side.
Short and on middle, Marnus pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Beaten! Quicker one outside off, Marnus pushes at it to get beaten.
Flighted ball around off, Labuschagne looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards point.
FOUR! Low full toss on middle, Labuschagne slams it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted and around off, Labuschagne comes forward to defend it out.
Shortish ball on off, Labuschagne cuts but finds the fielder.
Fuller and on the pads, Warner looks to flick dancing down the track but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball goes towards slip.
Short ball outside off, Warner works it through point for a single.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Fuller on middle, it is defended by Marnus by coming forward.
Fuller and on middle, it is defended.
Full and outside off, Marnus sweeps it towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Marnus plays it to mid on.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter ball on the pads, pushed towards mid-wicket.
On the pads, Warner works it towards mid on for a single.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off, Marnus cuts it to deep point for a single.
Short and outside off this one. Marnus cuts it wide of the deep cover fielder to pick a couple.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, turned towards mid-wicket.
Slightly shortish length, on the stumps line, Marnus taps it through point for a run.
Around off, Warner keeps it out.
Flighted, fuller and outside off, Warner drives but straight to the cover fielder.
Full toss on middle, Marnus flicks it to the long fielder for a single.
On off, Warner this time eases a single through mid on.
Short and outside off, Marnus cuts it to deep cover for a single.

NOT OUT! Day light between bat and pad. Flighted ball down the leg side. Warner looks to sweep but misses. Rizwan behind the wicket pouches the ball and then appeals. Not out says the umpire there but Rizwan feels that he heard something and insists his skipper for the referral. Nothing comes out of it as the replays roll in and confirm the same. The Ultra Edge shows no bat and Snicko confirms no tickle of the bat. Pakistan lose one of their review.
Fuller and outside off, pushed towards mid off.
FOUR! Flighted delivery on leg, Warner flicks it towards fine leg. The fielder chases it and tries to stop it with a slide but fails to stop it. It races away to the fence.
Full and on middle, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler. Shah picks the ball and throws it back to the striker's end but hits the batter. Smile exchanged between Marnus and the keeper there.
On the pads, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, Warner pushes it towards the off side to take a single.
On the pads, Labuschagne pads it away.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fuller and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Marnus this time pushes it wide of the mid on fielder for a single.
Fuller and outside off, Warner pushes it through covers and picks up a couple before the fielder can pick the ball and returns it to the keeper.
Loopy ball on off, Warner drives it through cover-point for a single.

EDGY FOUR! Tough chance this one. A quicker ball just outside off, Marnus looks to cut but gets an outside edge. The ball flies through the left of the first slip fielder and races to the third man fence.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full ball on off, Warner pushes it to long off for a run.
FOUR! Full and on middle, Marnus sweeps it to the deep mid-wicket fence. Nicely done.
Full and on middle, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on leg, Labuschagne offers no shot and pads it away.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full ball on middle, pushed towards cover.
On the pads, worked towards mid-wicket by David this time.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, Warner comes down the track and pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Around off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, pushed towards cover.
On off this time, Warner blocks it coming forward.
Shortish ball on middle, Warner cuts it to deep point and gets three runs.
Full and on middle, Marnus tucks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Full and on off this time, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid off.
On off, pushed to mid off once again.
Shortish length ball on the pads, Warner turns it towards square leg for a single.
Full and on off, pushed towards mid on for a run by Marnus this time.
On the hips, Warner works it straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Down the leg side. Warner nudges it towards square leg for a single.
Flighted ball on off, pushed towards cover.
Fuller and on off, it is defended.
Shaheen starts with a length ball just around off, Warner defends it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Beaten! Fuller ball, outside off. It draws Warner into the drive. He does so but is beaten.

Good length ball around off, Warner pushes it towards cover and takes a run. 150 comes up for Warner. He has utilized the one life he got due to the no ball brilliantly and continues going strength to strength.
Fuller and on off, it is defended.
Full length ball on middle, Marnus pushes it towards mid on.
Naseem starts with a fullish length ball on middle, Warner flicks it towards mid-wicket to pick a single.
In the channel outside off, ML leaves it alone.

FOUR! Fifth boundary for Marnus and he moves to 46. Poor ball it is. Short and wide outside off. Marnus guides it through the gap between point and gully. There is no protection at third man so a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball around off, Marnus taps it through point for a couple.
Outside off, Marnus makes another leave.
Beaten! Fullish ball outside off, Warner looks to drive but misses.
Full and around off, Warner punches it back to the bowler.
Play and a miss! Another ball in the channel outside off. Warner looks to cut away from the body to get beaten.
Fullish and on off, Warner blocks it out.
Fuller again and just outside off. Warner looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, Warner gets right behind the line of the delivery to defend it out.
Wide outside off to start with. Marnus lets it be.
Fuller and off, driven straight to mid off.
On a good length on off, Labuschagne taps it to point.
Outside off, Labuschagne offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on off, Marnus plays it towards point for a single.

Wow! What happened there. How lucky is Warner here? A good length ball which came in sharply. Warner though thought he has the stumps covered and shoulders arms. The ball kisses the off pole but the bail stays firm on the stumps. Warner survives.
Bowls it down the leg side, Labuschagne looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on off, Marnus looks to defend but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Was there an inside edge? Not sure.
FOUR! Sixth half century in Tests for Labuschagne. He gets a low full toss on middle. Marnus flicks it to the mid-wicket fence to reach the milestone.
Fuller this time, Labuschagne this time punches it through mid on for a couple of runs.
Outside off, it is left alone.
In the channel again. Marnus lets it be. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Imran starts with a length ball outside off, Warner watchfully lets it go to the keeper.
Gets closer to off pole but slightly shortish on length. Warner covers his stumps and lets it be.
This one is on off, Warner blocks it onto the pitch off his back foot.
In the channel outside off this time. Warner shoulders arms.
Fuller length and just outside off. Warner leans to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fullish and outside off, inviting a drive from Warner. He though shows no interest and lets it go. A maiden over to start.
He starts with a full length ball on off, Labuschagne comes forward and defends.
First run of the day, in the form of a quick single. Another fuller length ball outside off, Marnus pushes it towards mid off and takes a quick single.
Length ball on middle, Warner defends it out.
Shortish length ball around off, Warner stands tall and taps it on the off side.
Fuller ball on middle, Warner pushes it towards mid on and takes a quick single. Pakistani fielders need to do better to prevent these singles.
Short and outside off, it comes back in but not enough to make Marnus play.
Shortish length on off this one, Warner taps it towards mid off.
Fullish length and on off, blocked towards extra cover this time by David.
Some late movement there but after going past the batter. Good length delivery and outside off. Warner lets it be. It comes in after it goes past Warner.
Another ball in the channel outside off. Warner shoulders arms and watches the ball all the way to the gloves of the keeper.
Third leave of the over. Another ball in the tight zone outside off. Warner does not fiddle with it.
Fullish one and just outside off. Warner makes another leave after covering his stumps. No runs in the first two overs of Imran.
Full and on off, ML defends it towards point.
FOUR! Bang! First boundary of the day. Shaheen overpitches this one on off, Marnus drives it superbly wide of the mid off fielder. It races to the fence in a jiffy.
Around off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
FOUR! Second of the over. Full and outside off, Marnus creams it through cover-point to bag another boundary. 100-run stand is up between the two. Another brilliant partnership.
Shortish length ball on off, Marnus goes on the back foot to block.
Short and on middle this time, Labuschagne pulls it to deep square leg for an easy run.
Good length ball, closer to the off pole. Labuschagne bunts it onto the pitch on the off side.
Landed around off on a length, Marnus gets behind the line of the delivery to defend.
Full ball on off, Marnus is solid in his defense once again.
Full and on the pads, Marnus whips it through mid-wicket and wide of the mid on fielder. The deep square leg fielder runs to his left and saves a single. Three runs taken.
In the channel outside off, Warner lets it be.
Good length ball on middle and leg. Warner looks to tuck it towards the leg side but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad.
Well directed bouncer, just around off. Marnus does well to sway away.
Good length ball and around off, Labuschagne taps it towards point.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Short and around off, Marnus rides on the bounce and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Good length ball on off, Labuschagne punches it back to the bowler.
Another quick single. Excellent running between the wickets. Fullish ball outside off, Marnus drives it towards mid off and takes off for a quick run.
Fuller and on middle, Labuschagne pushes it towards mid on.
FOUR! Poor bowling this, too easy for Marnus. Looks to bowl the bouncer but hardly any pace and height to trouble Labuschagne. He pulls it to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Another quick run! Good length ball on middle, ML tucks it right of the mid on fielder and takes off for a single. The fielder there fumbles but no extra run taken.
On off, Warner keeps it out. He is looking in no hurry.
Fuller and very close to off pole but Warner is sure about his stumps as he shoulders arms.
Beaten! Beautiful delivery. Back of a length ball around off, Marnus stays on the back foot and looks to cut but misses to put any bat on ball.

Good length ball on off and middle, Marnus looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball goes towards square leg. A couple of runs taken. Excellent aggressive running from the Aussie pair.
Outside off and on a length, Labuschagne lets it be.
Another ball in the channel outside off. Marnus makes another leave.
Outside the off stump once again, Marnus once again leaves it alone.
On middle, Marnus turns it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.

FOUR! Superbly timed! Marnus gets to his highest Test score. An overpitched delivery outside off. Marnus shuffles to the leg side to make room and cream it through covers for a boundary. The lead has crossed 100 for Australia.
Full again, pushed towards cover.
Beaten! Slower through the air this one and pitches on off and turns away as Marnus brings his bat down to defend.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and on off, Marnus picks another couple of runs as he drives it right of the cover fielder.
On middle, Marnus comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Starts with a length ball outside off, Warner lets it be.
Shortish length ball around off, Warner stays on the back foot to defend.
Goes round the wicket and bowls a good length ball coming into the left-hander. David tucks it towards mid-wicket and calls for a quick single. Only the second run for Warner this morning.
Good length delivery on off, Marnus keeps it out.

Beauty! Need to continue bowling there to get the outside edge. Just behind the good length area and outside off. It pitches there and as it comes closer to the poke of Marnus it goes away to beat the outside edge.
Around off, Marnus this time is solid in his defense.
On middle, Warner taps it onto the pitch on the off side.
Flighted and on off, Warner lunges forward and pushes it towards cover.
Shortish length on off, Warner cuts it towards point and changes end.
Fuller and outside off, Labuschagne drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Fuller and on off, Marnus looks to drive but it goes towards mid-wicket off the inner half of the bat for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Warner keeps it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length delivery on off, Marnus defends it out.
Outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
Third consecutive leave for Marnus Labuschagne. Outside off again, Marnus lets it go.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne drives it towards mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside off, Labuschagne looks to cut but misses it. It was too close to cut.
FOUR! Shot of the morning! Fuller and just outside off, Marnus whips it wide of the mid on fielder and it races to the fence in a jiffy. Marnus enters into the nervous 90s.
Flatter and outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
Shortish outside off ball. Marnus cuts but straight to the point fielder.
Around off, Labuschagne comes forward and defends it out.

Huge appeal for caught behind but the umpire is not moved. Good length ball, going away after pitching. Warner flirts around this ball off the back foot without any feet movement. The ball goes past the outside edge and Naseem roars out an appeal. He is confident but the umpire deems it not out. Naseem feels there is some edge and wants the skipper to review. However, the skipper thinks, thinks and then decides against the review. A good call that one as replays roll in to show that there was no edge on that one.
Another beauty! This one is angled into Warner. It is a fullish length ball, Warner goes for the drive but misses.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

OUT! Caught! The 16-year-old strikes. What a delivery this one to get his maiden Test wicket. A superb bouncer on middle, Warner looks to sway away from the line of the delivery but it keeps coming into him. The ball catches the under edge and goes left of the keeper. Rizwan there dives to his left and pouches it superbly. Naseem went past the outside edge twice in the over and he deserved this wicket. They check for the no ball but this is a legal delivery. No respite for Warner this time and he needs to continue his walk to the pavilion. Standing ovation as he walks off after a brilliant century.
Full and on off, Smith pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on off, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Marnus drives it through covers for a single.
Floated delivery on off, Smith drives it to cover.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Smith comes down the track and blocks it.
Flighted delivery on off, Smith drives it back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Smith blocks it off the back foot.
Short and outside off, Marnus taps it towards point off the back foot.
Good length around off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Bouncer and on middle, Marnus pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Another superb bouncer and the world no.1 Test batsman gets a stare from the 16-year-old there. Short ball on middle, Smith drops his hands and sways away from the line of the ball.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Outside off again, Smith shoulders arms to this one.
Tossed up delivery on off, Marnus plays it to point.

NOT OUT! Labuschagne survives. Flighted delivery on off, Marnus looks to defend but misses it and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his finger. Labuschagne takes the review straightaway. Hot Spot rolls in and it shows there is a clear inside edge which means that the on-field umpire has to overturn the decision. An excellent review this one.
Short and outside off, Marnus cuts but straight to the fielder who lets the ball go through him for a single.
FOUR! Off the mark in style! Fullish ball around off, Smith comes down the track and whips it to the mid-wicket fence nicely.

OUT! Bowled' em! Yasir strikes and removes the big fish. He has been excellent this morning and has got a reward for that with the wicket of world's no.1 Test batsman. A flighted ball on off, Smith after getting that boundary looks to stay in the attacking mode. He looks to whip it on the leg side but misses the line of the ball completely. The ball goes behind and disturbs the off pole. Two wickets in quick time for Pakistan.

Almost another one. Flighted ball on middle, Wade looks to work it on the leg side but does so from the inner half of the bat and uppishly. Just away from the short leg fielder there. End of an excellent over from Yasir.
On middle, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball, closer to off pole. Wade covers his stumps and makes another leave. A good leave that one.
Full and on off, Wade drives it towards mid off and takes a quick single to get off the mark.
Short and on middle, Labuschagne pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Flighted ball on the pads, Marnus nudges it behind square leg for a single. 3 away from his maiden Test ton.
Flighted and on the pads, Wade looks to work it down the leg side but gets a soft leading edge which balloons in the air and drops on the off side.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Goes back and defends this quicker one on middle by getting right behind the line of the ball.
FOUR! First one for Wade. Juicy fuller ball outside off. Wade leans into the drive and hammers it through the cover region and into the fence.
Full and on off, driven straight to mid off.
Outside off, Marnus offers no shot to this one.
On a good length and outside off, Labuschagne lets it go.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne drives it back towards the bowler.

Edged but Four!  There it is. Maiden Test ton for Marnus Labuschagne. What an innings this has been from the Aussie number 3. The hometown boy raises his arms and soaks in all the applause from the crowd. His family is in the attendance and they love it. This is a fuller ball and outside off, Marnus looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. As soon as Labuschagne sees the ball going through the slip cordon, he raises his bat and celebrates. After 4 half tons, he finally gets to the three figure mark in Test match cricket.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Around off, Marnus defends it out.
FOUR! Nice shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Wade comes down the track and flicks it through mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on off, Wade blocks it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Wade defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Wade keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Wade defends it out.
On off, Wade defends it off the back foot.
Fuller delivery on off, Labuschagne is solid behind his defense.
Fullish ball around off, Marnus is confident about his stumps as he lets it go behind for the keeper to collect.
On off, Marnus pushes it towards mid on
Fuller and on off, Labuschagne drives it back to the bowler.

Just in front of Babar Azam at gully. Another fuller ball just outside off, a leg cutter this one. Marnus looks to drive but gets an outside edge which flies towards gully but falls just short of Azam there.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Wade goes on the back foot and punches it through cover to bag his third boundary of the innings.
Fullish and just around off, Wade turns it towards point with an angled bat for a single.
Flatter one around off, Marnus lunges forward to keep it out.
On middle, it is defended.

Nicely kicked away! A quicker one on middle, slightly shortish length. Marnus goes back and defends it onto the pitch. However, it seems like it might go on the stumps. Seeing that, Labuschagne kicks it away.
Flighted and outside off, Labuschagne tucks it towards point.
Full delivery on off, Wade drives it to covers.
Outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on off, Wade blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Wade does well to duck under it.
Length delivery on middle, Wade flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Good length delivery on off, Marnus defends it to covers.
FOUR! Good improvisation. Flighted delivery on middle, Wade plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted ball on middle, Wade looks to defend on the off side but gets it towards the leg side off the inner half of the bat.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tossed up on off, Wade pushes it towards extra cover.
Around off, Wade keeps it out.
Flighted fullish ball on off, Wade taps it towards the off side and takes a quick single.
Starts with a shortish length ball on middle, Wade nudges it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Fuller and outside off, Marnus drives it nicely but straight to cover.
Full and on off, Labuschagne comes forward and keeps it out.
On the pads, pushed towards mid on.
On middle, Marnus gets right behind the line of the ball to defend it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted ball on off and middle, Wade goes right back and keeps it out.
Another ball turning into the left-hander. Wade tucks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Short and outside off, Marnus cuts it to deep cover for a single.
Quicker one on the pads, Wade looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
FOUR! Poor ball and punished! Short and down the leg side. Wade hammers it behind square leg to earn another boundary. The lead for Australia now crosses 150.
Full and on the pads, Wade flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Full and down the leg side. Wade sits down and guides it towards fine leg to pick a couple of easy run.
On off, Wade defends it out off the back foot
Full and on off, Wade once again is solid behind the line of the ball.
Full and on middle, Wade pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Wade pushes it towards point. One more ball before Lunch.
Shortish length outside off, tapped towards cover. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Starts with a shortish ball outside off, Marnus punches it towards mid off and takes a single.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler by Wade.
Another fuller ball on stump line. Wade blocks it coming forward.
Flighted on middle, Wade comes down the track and defends
On middle, it is defended.
Full and around off, Wade looks to reverse sweep but cannot do that cleanly. Almost dragged the ball on the stumps off his gloves. It goes towards short fine leg.
Starts with a length ball outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Landed around middle, Labuschagne tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length delivery on middle, Wade flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus drives it towards mid on.
Full again on middle, Labuschagne flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Fullish ball outside off, it is left alone.
On the pads, tucked towards the leg side.
Full on the pads again, flicked straight to square leg.
Another ball on the pads, worked towards square leg.
Down the leg side again. Not great lines. Labuschagne turns it towards fine leg for a single. 400 up for Australia.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Quicker one this time, Wade defends it out coming forward.
Shortish length ball outside off, Marnus taps it to mid on.
On the pads of Marnus on a length. He tucks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery outside off, Wade offers no shot to this one.
Outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Fourth consecutive leave for Matthew Wade. Outside off again, Wade lets it go.

FOUR! Full ball on middle, Marnus gets in position and sweeps it towards fine leg. Shaheen Afridi from deep square leg hares at the ball to cut it off with a sliding effort but can't do that. The ball eventually touches the ropes.
Slightly short, Marnus blocks it off the back foot.
Quicker one on the pads, Labuschagne tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
On middle, Wade goes right back to keep it out.
Tossed up on middle, Wade defends it off the front foot.

Excellent effort from Shan Masood. Short and wide outside off. Wade cuts it through point. Masood hares after the ball and looks to pull the ball back in. Three runs taken. 50-run stand is up between Matthew Wade and Marnus Labuschagne.
Shortish length ball outside off, Wade comes towards the off side to cut the angle and block it away.
Outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Outside off again, Wade lets it go.
Full delivery on middle, Wade flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Outside off, Wade does not bother to play at that.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Flighted delivery on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! Tonked it away! Flighted ball on middle, Wade skips down the track and send it sailing over the long on fence. First six of the innings.
Fuller and outside off, Wade drives it straight to covers.
Quicker and shortish ball on the pads, Wade punches it wide of long on and picks a couple of runs.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Fuller and just outside off, Wade pushes it towards point.
Outside off, Marnus leaves it alone.
On a good length on middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Marnus defends it out.
FOUR! Hammered away! Short delivery on middle and leg, Labuschagne pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Short of the match so far! Fullish length on off, Labuschagne gets in the position and drills it straight down the ground. No chance for the mid off fielder there. Brilliant batting.
Around off and on a length, Marnus gets behind the line of the ball to keep it out.
Flighted delivery on leg, it turns away, Wade looks to flick but gets an inside edge. It goes towards fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Fuller and outside off, Marnus drives it well but straight to the fielder at cover.
Full and on off, Labuschagne sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket. Shaheen from deep square leg goes after he ball and misfields which allows the batters to pick the third.
This time Wade sweeps it uppishly towards fine leg for a single.
On middle and leg of Marnus. He guides it behind square for a single.
On the pads once again, Wade nudges it towards square lg.
Good length ball around off and middle. Marnus looks to work it towards the leg side but gets a soft leading edge which goes towards the off side.
Fullish ball on middle, Labuschagne tucks it towards mid on for a quick run. The fielder has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses.
Good length ball angled into the batter. Wade is late in trying to tuck it towards the leg side. The ball goes on to hit him high on the thigh pads.
Length and around off, it is defended solidly.
Bouncer on middle. Wade ducks under it. Shaheen stares, Wade returns the favor with a few words.
Bouncer but outside off this time, Wade ducks under it easily.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Marnus blocks it off the back foot.
Short and outside off, Marnus this time guides it towards third man for a couple of runs.
Full and on the pads, Labuschagne flicks it past the mid-wicket fielder for a couple of runs.
Quicker and shorter one. Marnus goes on the back foot block it away.

Fractionally short of full, around middle, Labuschagne goes back and works it behind square leg. Now, Afridi at deep backward square leg anticipates incorrectly and runs to his left but the ball lands on the turf and spins away, to his right. So Shaheen has to put sudden brakes then run in the opposite direction which helps the batters steam an extra run. Cannot blame the young man entirely. It is his first tour to Australia and it does take time to get used to large grounds. Kamran Akmal would have been a helpful here as he would have shouted - 'Ghoomegi!'.
Shortish length ball on off, Labuschagne goes back and keeps it out.
On a good length on off, Wade taps it to point.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery outside off, Wade drives it through point for a boundary. Matthew Wade moves to 49.
Good length delivery on off, Wade defends it out.

Fifty for Matthew Wade! His 5th half ton in Tests. He gets there by tucking this good length ball on middle towards mid-wicket for a single. He will look to convert this into a big one to help Australia take a massive lead.
Fullish ball on middle, driven nicely but straight to mid on.
This one is full on off, Marnus drives it straight to cover this time.
Flighted delivery on off, Wade defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Wade nudges it to the leg side.
Floated delivery on middle, Wade plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get three runs.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Wade sweeps it towards fine leg. The batsmen take a run.
FOUR! Nice shot. Flighted delivery on off, Marnus guides it towards third man for a boundary.
Good length ball just outside off, Wade looks to defend coming forward but ball takes the inside edge and goes behind square leg for a single.
Short delivery on middle, Marnus pulls it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple. 100-run stand is up between Wade and Labuschagne.
Beaten! Rare loose shot from Labuschagne. Fullish length ball just outside off, inviting the drive. Labuschagne obliges and drives but fails to put any bat on ball.
Another fullish length and slightly wider than the last ball. Marnus this time looks to cut but is beaten.
Shortish length around off, Marnus taps it towards point and takes a single.
Yorker outside off, Wade digs it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Marnus defends it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Marnus drives it through mid off for a single.
Floated delivery on off, Wade defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Good shot. Flighted delivery on off, Wade plays a reverse sweep towards third man for a boundary.
Loopy delivery on middle, Wade flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated delivery on middle, Wade plays a reverse sweep towards third man for a single.
On a good length on off, Wade defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.

Full delivery outside off, Wade pushes it towards covers and takes a quick single. The fielder throws it towards Wade at the non-striker's end but the throw finds the left hand of Wade. Wade looks in pain there as he removes his gloves and checks his hand. Probably the fielder apologizes and Wade accepts the apology there with a thumbs up.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne drives it back towards the bowler.
Shortish length just outside off, Marnus taps is onto the pitch on the off side.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted delivery on middle, Wade defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Wade comes down the track and drives it towards mid off for a single.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it through mid off. The batsmen cross ends.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted delivery on middle, Wade comes down the track and blocks it.

OUT! Wade departs! A wicket out of nowhere. Wade was in search of quick runs. He once again tries using his feet there. Sohail judged that nicely and dropped his length just short. Wade then looks to guide it towards third man. He gets a faint outside edge which goes behind. Rizwan in his first attempt misses out but eventually manages to hold on in the second attempt. The stand is broken. Wade walks back with shake of his head. But a nice innings nonetheless from the left-hander.
Tossed up outside off, Labuschagne offers no shot to this one.
Flighted delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
IN THE AIR BUT SAFE! Floated delivery on off, Marnus lofts it over covers but it lands safely in no man's land. The batsmen take a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Head flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Full and on middle, Marnus drives it straight to mid on.
Shortish length ball on middle, Marnus turns it towards square leg and takes a single.
Floated delivery on off, Marnus guides it towards short third man. The batsmen take a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Head pushes it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Head flicks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Tossed up outside off, Head looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on off, Travis defends it off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Head flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Short ball on middle, Head pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and picks a couple.
Quicker one outside off, it is left alone.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and outside off, Head stays on the back foot and punches it through cover-point to bag his first boundary of the inning.
Full and on the pads, Head flicks it towards square leg.
Fullish and on off, Head comes forward and blocks it towards cover.
Fullish and on off, Head comes forward and blocks it towards cover.
Tossed up delivery on off, Head plays it back towards the bowler.

Excellent effort from the keeper there. He ran all the way from his position to the third man fence. A flighted fuller ball just outside off, Head looks to drive but the ball takes the outside edge and races towards the third man fence.
150 up for Labuschagne. He is playing a gem of an innings here. He gets there by tapping the short ball towards point for a single.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the backfoot.
Short and on the pads, Head turns it towards the leg side for a single.
Around off, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on off, Head punches it towards the bowler but Yasir Shah misfields and concedes a single.
Floated delivery on off, Marnus plays a reverse sweep towards third man. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Head nudges it to the leg side.
Full delivery on middle, Travis drives it through mid on. The batsmen take a run.
Flighted delivery on middle, Marnus flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Full delivery outside off, Head drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Flighted outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Excellent running! And that takes Pakistan's total over 500. On the pads, Marnus turns it towards square leg and takes a quick couple.
Full and on off, it is defended.
Driven through mid on by the batsman. They pick up a single.
Fuller ball outside off, Head pushes it towards mid on.
Full and on the pads, nudged towards square leg.
Shortish length ball, angled into the batter. Marnus stands tall and blocks it away.
Short and outside off, cut to deep point for a single by Marnus.
Full and on middle this one. Head drives it firmly but straight to mid on.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Fuller ball outside off, Head drives it through point and takes a single.
Good length ball on the pads, Labuschagne turns it towards the leg side for a single.
Short and outside off, Labuschagne cuts it towards deep point for a run.
On off, Head comes forward and defends it solidly.
Another ball on the stumps line, Head keeps it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

OUT! Caught! Excellent take from Rizwan behind the wicket and Sohail has his second. Not the ball you get wickets but Rizwan grabs it nicely there. Down the leg side, Head looks to glance it fine but gets faintest of edge behind. Rizwan moves to his right and pouches it superbly. They appeal and the umpire raises his finger instantly.
Shortish ball on middle, Paine goes behind and blocks it towards the leg side.
Shortish length ball just outside off, Labuschagne blocks it off the back foot.
Short ball on middle, Marnus swivels and pulls it to deep square leg and scamper back for a couple of runs.
Length ball just outside off, Marnus keeps it out.
Around off and slightly shortish length. Marnus taps it towards the slip cordon with soft hands.
Landed just outside off, Marnus keeps it out easily.
Full and on off, Labuschagne drives it towards mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Paine defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Paine flicks it towards square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Full delivery on middle, Marnus drives it through mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
Floated delivery on off, Paine defends it out.
Bowls it down the leg side, Paine looks to flick but misses it.
Short on off, Paine cuts it through point for a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Paine keeps it out.

FOUR! First boundary for the Australian skipper. Short and wide outside off. Paine rocks back on his back foot and hammers it through the cover region. Two fielders gives it a chase but the ball wins the race to the fence.
On the pads, Paine nudges it towards square leg and takes a run
Flighted fuller ball on middle, Marnus drives it well but the cover fielder dives to his left to make a stop.
On middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.
On the pads, turned towards square leg.
Flighted delivery on off, Paine drives it through mid off for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Good batting from Marnus. Flighted delivery on middle, Labuschagne comes down the track and lofts it over mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Marnus. And if the last one was use of power this one is a delicate touch. Quicker ball and outside off. Labuschagne waits on the back foot and guides it to the third man fence.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. One run added to the total.
FOUR! Tossed up delivery on leg, Paine looks to sweep but gets a top edge. It goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted ball on middle, Marnus looks to drive it towards the off side but it goes towards mid-wicket off the inner half of his bat.
This time he eases a single through mid on by pushing this fuller ball on middle.
Shortish length ball, angled into Paine. He goes back and flicks but straight to mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, Paine pushes it right of the bowler for a single.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.

Huge appeal for leg before wicket but the umpire shows no interest there. Flighted fuller ball on middle, Marnus looks to sweep but misses. The ball hits his front pad. Iftikhar makes a loud appeal along with the keeper but the umpire says not out. Pakistan skipper Azhar, keeper Rizwan and the bowler converge together and then eventually decide against taking the DRS.
Flighted delivery on middle, Paine defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Tim offers a forward defense on this one.
Floated delivery on middle, Paine flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off, Paine keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Paine defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Paine defends it off the back foot. TEA ON DAY 3!
Full delivery outside off, Marnus looks to defend but misses it.
FOUR! Pierced the gap superbly. Full ball on middle, he flicks it between mid-wicket and mid on. The ball races to the fence.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries now. This one is even better. Another fuller ball on middle, Marnus flicks it brilliantly to the deep mid-wicket fence once again. Brilliant batting. The lead is 300 now.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.
Short and outside off, Labuschagne cuts but finds gully on the bounce.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus comes across the off stump and tucks it right of mid on to take a single.
Flighted around off, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish ball outside off, Marnus this time taps it to long on and takes a run.
On off, pushed towards cover by Paine.
Quicker ball on middle, Paine keeps it out.
Big turn but wide outside off. Paine lets it be.
Full and on the pads, Paine dead bats it to the left of the short leg fielder.
Yorker outside off. Marnus looks to dig out but misses it.
Another yorker outside off. ML this time jams it out towards first slip.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus lofts this one over the mid off fielder to pick a couple. Did not time that well but good enough to scamper back for the second.
Full and on the pads, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! Caught! The skipper departs now! Shortish length ball on middle, Paine looks to pull but the ball takes the under edge and then hits the pads. It lobs towards third slip where Asad Shafiq takes the simplest of catches.
Full and on off, Cummins drives it nicely but straight to mid off.
Outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Quicker one on off, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Labuschagne looks to whip on the leg side but ends up slicing it towards long off uppishly. A single taken.
Flatter one outside off, Cummins guides it towards short third man.
On middle, Cummins pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball on middle, Pat comes forward and defends it out.
Shortish length ball outside off, Marnus looks to pull but he nowhere near the ball. Misses it completely.

OUT! Caught! Hearbreak for Marnus in front of the home crowd. A soft dismissal this one but what a fantastic innings. The crowd gets up and applauds the brilliant innings. Labuschagne raises his bat as he trudges off the ground. Full ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to guide it to the third man fence, in search of quick runs. He reached out to play but manages to guide it straight to Azam at gully who makes no mistake. He stands still at the crease thinking what has he done as the umpire check for the front foot no ball. The front foot is fine and Labuschagne has to walk back.
Yorker around off, Starc digs it out.
Back of a length ball outside off, Starc lets it be.
On a good length on off, Starc defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Starc plays it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on off, Cummins drives it through mid off. The batsmen cross ends.
Floated delivery on off, Starc cuts it through point. The batsmen get three runs.
Tossed up delivery on off, Cummins drives it through covers. The batsmen get three runs. Good running between the wickets.

FOUR BYES! That's gone through everyone. Pitches on middle. Starc looks to defend but the ball goes through his defense and over the stumps. Rizwan fails to collect too and it races to the fine leg fence.
The batsman has nudged the ball fine down the leg side. They manage to come back for the second.

OUT! LBW! Yasir has his third. Brilliant bowling. He pitches it on middle and tossed it up nicely. Starc looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. The appeal follows and umpire raises the finger instantly. Starc reviews after a brief chat with Cummins. Here comes the replay, Hot Spot shows no bat. No deflection on the Snicko. Now, the Ball Tracker, pitching in line and going on to hit the middle and leg pole. Starc has to go. He takes a review along with him. No declaration though.
Length delivery on leg, Cummins flicks it towards fine leg. The batsmen take a run.
On a good length on off, Lyon defends it out.
On a length on middle, Lyon flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Cummins drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Bowls a bumper, Cummins does well to duck under it.
On a good length on off, Cummins defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Tossed up outside off, Lyon guides it towards third man for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on middle, Lyon defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on off, Lyon keeps it out.
BEATEN! Tossed up delivery outside off, Lyon looks to defend but misses it.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Outside off, Lyon shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards point off the back foot.
Another length ball, closer to the off pole line, Cummins taps it towards cover.

OUT! Caught! Pat Cummins goes now and Imran gets his first wicket of the game. Fourth catch for Rizwan behind the wickets. A fullish ball outside off, Cummins goes for the expansive drive away from his body. He manages an outside edge which goes behind. Rizwan gets down and snaffles it inches above the ground.
Good length ball on off, Hazlewood looks to defend but manages it towards square leg off the inner half of the bat for a single.
Bouncer down the leg side. Lyon looks to pull but misses.
Another bouncer and on middle and leg. Lyon this time hooks towards deep square leg for a run.
Full and straight on off, Lyon pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, Lyon keeps it out.
Full again on off too. Lyon pushes it back to the bowler once again. Yasir misfields and allows a single through mid off.
Yorker on middle, Hazlewood blocks it nicely.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Creamed through mid off. Full and just outside off, Hazlewood slams it left of the mid off fielder.
Short ball on middle, Lyon pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
In the channel around off, Hazlewood looks to block off the back foot but makes no connection.
On a length on off, Hazlewood plays it to covers.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Hazlewood looks to punch but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Josh keeps it out.
Play and a miss! Short and outside off, Hazlewood looks to cut but misses it.
Flighted delivery on middle, Lyon flicks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Good shot. Floated delivery on middle, Lyon plays a sweep through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on off, Lyon drives it through covers for a run.

OUT! LBW! Not much use of the review. Umpire's call it is, on height and Australia's batting innings ends. Flighted delivery on off, Hazlewood looks to defend but misses it as the ball turns in and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his finger. Hazlewood has a long look at his partner and almost as if to suggest that there is a review left, so let's take it, opts for the same. There is nothing on Hot Spot, or Snicko. Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on height, as the ball is clipping the top of leg stump. The original decision will stay as it is. AUSTRALIA ARE ALL OUT FOR 580.

Ouch! That would've hurt. Starc starts with a short of a length delivery on middle, Masood looks to work it down the leg side but is late in the shot. The ball goes to hit on the stomach. Masood hops in pain.
Bouncer this time but is outside off, Masood drops his wrists and sways away from the line of the ball.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Shan Masood. Full again on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Masood defends it out.
Bowls a bouncer outside off, Masood lets it sail through to the keeper.
Good length delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on off, Azhar plays it towards point. The batsmen cross ends.
Outside off, Masood offers no shot to this one.
Outside off again, Masood leaves it alone.
Bowls a bouncer down the leg side, Azhar does well to duck under it.
On a good length and outside off, Ali lets it go.
Outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
FOUR! Lovely shot from the skipper. Full and outside off, Azhar drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Yes, just as we suspected, it is umpire's call on height. There's the first one. Starc strikes and sends the Pakistani skipper back to the pavilion. On a good length on middle, Azhar looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The Australians roar out a loud appeal and the umpire agrees. Azhar Ali does not look sure as he walks towards the non-striker. Seems like he will not review that one, but hello, with just two seconds left on the timer, he signals the 'T'. Let's see what the replays show. There is nothing on Snicko and Hot Spot. Ball Tracker shows that it is pitching in line and clipping the top of the middle stump. Pakistan retain the review but their skipper has to depart. Early strike for Australia, exactly what they would've wanted.
Good length delivery on off, Sohail defends it towards covers and takes a run.
On a good length on off, Sohail guides it towards third man. Lyon chases it, slides and does well to pull it back before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs.
Length delivery on off, Masood punches it towards point. The batsmen take a single.
Good length delivery on off, Sohail defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on off, Haris keeps it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Sohail blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Haris does well to duck under it.
Short delivery on leg, Masood pulls it through square leg. Pat Cummins in the deep does well to stop it with a dive. The batsmen get two runs.
Length delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! Nice shot. Length delivery on off, Sohail guides it towards third man for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Unbelievable. Almost an action replay of his dismissal in the first innings. Sohail falls to another poor shot. He cannot believe it as he shuts his eyes and takes a few seconds before trudging off. Short delivery outside off, Sohail looks to punch it off the back foot and away from his body. The ball shapes away just a hint and all Haris can manage is a faint outside edge which goes behind. Paine gobbles it comfortably and celebrates. Sohail got out to Starc in a similar fashion in the first innings as well. Problems for Pakistan early on.
Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Shafiq does well to duck under it. Tim Paine does well to stop it with one hand.
On a good length on off, Asad taps it to point.
Full delivery on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on off, Masood punches it to point.

Shortish length ball around off, Asad taps it towards point off the back foot.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Shafiq looks to drive but misses it and gets beaten on the inside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! There goes the third one. The half centurion of the first innings goes for a duck. Cummins is the man with the wicket now. On a good length on off, going away. Shafiq pokes at it with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards Smith at second slip. He makes no mistake in gobbling that.
Good length delivery on off, Azam defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Babar lets it go.
Short of a length delivery, Masood pulls it to mid-wicket.

On a good length on off, Masood looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third slip on one bounce.

Short delivery on leg, Masood pulls it through square leg. The batsmen get three runs. Good running between the wickets.
Good length delivery on middle, Azam defends it off the back foot.
Bowls it down the leg side, Azam lets it go.
Outside off, Azam does not offer any shot to this one.
On a good length on middle, Azam defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Babar shoulders arms to this one.
Short delivery on middle, Masood pulls it over mid-wicket. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Good length delivery on middle, Azam blocks it off the back foot.

Good length delivery outside off, Babar does not bother to play at that.
BEATEN! On a good length and just outside off, Azam looks to defend but misses it due to the inward movement on this one.

FOUR! Excellent shot. Full on off, Azam drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Good length delivery on off, Babar defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Azam lets it go.
Full delivery outside off, Azam drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Length delivery on middle, Azam flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen get a single.
Bowls a bumper outside off, Masood sways away from it.

NO BALL! Bowls a bouncer down the leg side, Babar ducks under it. It is called no ball for height.

Short delivery outside off, Azam cuts it through point. Nathan Lyon chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Bowls a yorker on middle, Masood does well to dig it out.

Full delivery outside off, Azam drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs. Good running between the wickets.
Bowls it down the leg side, Masood lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Shan defends it off the back foot.
Length delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nicely put away! Short delivery outside off, Masood cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle, Masood blocks it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Turn and bounce on this one. Flighted delivery outside off, it pitches on the rough, Masood looks to defend but misses it.

NOT OUT! Shan Masood is safe. Flighted delivery on off, Masood looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes low to Smith at first slip. He gets down and catches it. Or has he? He is not sure. The umpires converge and ask help from the third umpire. The soft signal is not out. First they check the legality, yes, it is a fair ball. There is an outside edge as well. It goes to Smith low and dies in front of him. Here comes the replay. Seems like it has kissed the turf there before going in the hands of Smith. The third umpire is checking a few angles before making a call. Yes, not out flashes the screen and Masood will heave a sigh of relief.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, it is defended.
FOUR! On a good length on off, Azam looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards the third man region for a boundary.
Outside off, Babar shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Azam looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off, Azam lets it go.
On a good length on off, Babar defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Babar keeps it out. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Good turn and bounce first up. It pitches on the turf and turns away as Masood leaves it alone.
Short delivery on off, Masood cuts it through point. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Flighted delivery on off, Masood defends it off the back foot.
